column5: A phenominal week of walleye fishing is what I expected, and Lac Seul didn’t dissapoint. At times, we were hauling in a fish a minute in our 3 man boat. (The 24’s and 25″ inchers slowed us down…) What an incredible fishery. Good numbers and fantastic size this year. a pair of 27.5″ fish, plus many, MANY 24-27 inchers as well. What a great week!
Glad you had a good trip ! That picture of the sun is outstanding.
Awesome trip men!! Very cool pics! I bet the arms are bit wore out.
Nice Fish!We just got back Friday, We had great weather and the fishing was awsome.We fished Mckinsey bay.Did you guys stay up near there ?
great fish and pics.  you should have that last pic framed and hung.
beautiful! looks like an awesome time was had.
Taylor island area… not sure where Mckinsey bay is.
Very cool… looks like you guys were blanked by the smoke from all the fires as well. Makes for some gorgeous sunsets!
Actually, it wasn’t bad. We smelled it one day after the winds shifted and had one great sunset… Otherwise, it was crystal clear the rest of the week.
